<subSubSection id="C3006544FF9AFF9898BC700FFE40A967" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BA536CFFF9AFF9898BC700FFE40A967" blockId="1.[151,1436,152,1769]" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">
<emphasis id="B96EEADDFF9AFF9898BC700FFEEFA944" bold="true" box="[199,327,325,348]" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is from the Latin “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C1A4D4CFF9AFF989B7D700FFCF9A944" box="[774,849,325,348]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pelecium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="igneus">igneus</taxonomicName>
”, which means “on fire”, in reference to the reddish reflexes on pronotum and head.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3006544FF9AFF9898BC70C0FE1AAAAF" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BA536CFFF9AFF9898BC70C0FE1AAAAF" blockId="1.[151,1436,152,1769]" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">
<emphasis id="B96EEADDFF9AFF9898BC70C0FE94A9B9" bold="true" box="[199,316,394,417]" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
A medium sized species (
<quantity id="4CE29B2AFF9AFF989A1F70C0FD1CA9B9" box="[612,692,394,417]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" unit="mm" value="13.0">13 mm</quantity>
) distinguishable among other congeners by the combination of the following features: Fore body dorsum is bright metallic and thence contrasts sharply with the black elytra (
<figureCitation id="13212A4AFF9AFF989D7670E7FAE5A9DC" box="[1293,1357,429,452]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1827,1849]" captionTargetBox="[201,1368,320,1789]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[192,1395,311,1806]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Pelecium igneus Orsetti &amp; Lopes-Andrade sp. nov., male holotype. 1, 3 dorsal view 2, 4 ventral view. 3. Head, arrowhead points to excavations of frontal fovea 4. Detail of labial and maxillary palpomeres. Scale bars: 5 mm (1 − 2); 1 mm (3 − 4)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261701/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). Head with frontal impressions punctiform (
<figureCitation id="13212A4AFF9AFF989A5F709AFD29A9FF" box="[548,641,464,487]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1827,1849]" captionTargetBox="[201,1368,320,1789]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[192,1395,311,1806]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Pelecium igneus Orsetti &amp; Lopes-Andrade sp. nov., male holotype. 1, 3 dorsal view 2, 4 ventral view. 3. Head, arrowhead points to excavations of frontal fovea 4. Detail of labial and maxillary palpomeres. Scale bars: 5 mm (1 − 2); 1 mm (3 − 4)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261701/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Figs 1, 3</figureCitation>
), with a short and shallow excavation. Pronotum with median line shallow (
<figureCitation id="13212A4AFF9AFF9898E470B8FF76AA11" box="[159,222,498,521]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1827,1849]" captionTargetBox="[201,1368,320,1789]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[192,1395,311,1806]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Pelecium igneus Orsetti &amp; Lopes-Andrade sp. nov., male holotype. 1, 3 dorsal view 2, 4 ventral view. 3. Head, arrowhead points to excavations of frontal fovea 4. Detail of labial and maxillary palpomeres. Scale bars: 5 mm (1 − 2); 1 mm (3 − 4)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261701/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
), barely discernible, deeper posteriorly; basal impressions very shallow. Apical labial and maxillary palpomeres triangular (
<figureCitation id="13212A4AFF9AFF989974735FFEFAAA34" box="[271,338,533,556]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1827,1849]" captionTargetBox="[201,1368,320,1789]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[192,1395,311,1806]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Pelecium igneus Orsetti &amp; Lopes-Andrade sp. nov., male holotype. 1, 3 dorsal view 2, 4 ventral view. 3. Head, arrowhead points to excavations of frontal fovea 4. Detail of labial and maxillary palpomeres. Scale bars: 5 mm (1 − 2); 1 mm (3 − 4)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261701/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
). Adults of 
<emphasis id="B96EEADDFF9AFF9899AE735FFD9AAA34" box="[469,562,533,556]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">P. i gn e us</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C1A4D4CFF9AFF989A16735FFD74AA34" box="[621,732,532,556]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pelecium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="helenae">
<emphasis id="B96EEADDFF9AFF989A16735FFD74AA34" box="[621,732,532,556]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">P. helenae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are quite similar in the shape of the body, frontal fovea of head, median line and basal impressions of pronotum. However, in 
<taxonomicName id="4C1A4D4CFF9AFF989B4E7372FC3FAA57" box="[821,919,568,591]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pelecium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="igneus">
<emphasis id="B96EEADDFF9AFF989B4E7372FC3FAA57" box="[821,919,568,591]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">P. igneus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the lateral edges of pronotum are more arcuate near base, giving it a subcordate shape when seen from above. Moreover, in 
<taxonomicName id="4C1A4D4CFF9AFF989BB97310FB89AA69" box="[962,1057,602,625]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pelecium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="igneus">
<emphasis id="B96EEADDFF9AFF989BB97310FB89AA69" box="[962,1057,602,625]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">P. igneus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the elytra is comparatively rounder when seen from above and is shiny black, contrasting with its metallic reddish pronotum. In 
<taxonomicName id="4C1A4D4CFF9AFF989CF07337FB52AA8C" box="[1163,1274,636,660]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pelecium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="helenae">
<emphasis id="B96EEADDFF9AFF989CF07337FB52AA8C" box="[1163,1274,636,660]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">P. helenae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the dorsum is homogeneously violaceus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3006544FF9AFF9898BC7388FE34ADA9" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BA536CFFF9AFF9898BC7388FE34ADA9" blockId="1.[151,1436,152,1769]" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">
<emphasis id="B96EEADDFF9AFF9898BC7388FE53AAC1" bold="true" box="[199,507,706,729]" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">
Description, male 
<typeStatus id="54A1886DFF9AFF9899E27388FE53AAC1" box="[409,507,706,729]" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">holotype</typeStatus>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="13212A4AFF9AFF989A717388FDD2AAC1" box="[522,634,706,729]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStart-1="FIGURES 5 – 12" captionStartId-0="2.[151,258,1827,1849]" captionStartId-1="3.[151,258,1791,1813]" captionTargetBox-0="[201,1368,320,1789]" captionTargetBox-1="[204,1400,205,1756]" captionTargetId-0="figure@2.[192,1395,311,1806]" captionTargetId-1="figure@3.[185,1401,191,1770]" captionTargetPageId-0="2" captionTargetPageId-1="3" captionText-0="FIGURES 1 – 4. Pelecium igneus Orsetti &amp; Lopes-Andrade sp. nov., male holotype. 1, 3 dorsal view 2, 4 ventral view. 3. Head, arrowhead points to excavations of frontal fovea 4. Detail of labial and maxillary palpomeres. Scale bars: 5 mm (1 − 2); 1 mm (3 − 4)." captionText-1="FIGURES 5 – 12. Pelecium igneus Orsetti &amp; Lopes-Andrade sp. nov., male holotype. Aedeagus (5 – 8) 5. Dorsal view 6. Left lateral view 7. Ven tr a l v ie w 8. Right lateral view 9. Penis, right lateral view 10. Left paramere 11. Right paramere 12. Tergite IX. Scale bar: 0.5 mm." httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/261701/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/261702/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Figs 1–12</figureCitation>
). Fully pigmented adult. Measurements in mm: AL1-11: 0.81, 0.48, 0.55, 0.52, 0.56, 0.50, 0.44, 0.45, 0.43, 0.45, 0.65, EL 6.89, EW 5.18, lp2L 0.57, lp3L 0.83, lp3 
<geoCoordinate id="EE2E5008FF9AFF989C0873AFFB60AAE4" box="[1139,1224,741,764]" direction="west" orientation="longitude" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" precision="555" value="-0.51">W 0.51</geoCoordinate>
, mp3L 0.24, mp4L 0.68, mp4 
<geoCoordinate id="EE2E5008FF9AFF9899787242FEFEAB07" box="[259,342,776,799]" direction="west" orientation="longitude" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" precision="555" value="-0.46">W 0.46</geoCoordinate>
, PL 3.85, PW 3.83, SL 0.49, SW 0.67, TL 12.85. Ratio: TL/EW 2.48. 
<emphasis id="B96EEADDFF9AFF989C1B7242FB33AB07" bold="true" box="[1120,1179,776,799]" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Body</emphasis>
ovate and flat; discs of head and pronotum metallic wine reddish in dorsal view, with greenish and yellowish reflections along sides (
<figureCitation id="13212A4AFF9AFF989D317260FA22AB59" box="[1354,1418,810,833]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1827,1849]" captionTargetBox="[201,1368,320,1789]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[192,1395,311,1806]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Pelecium igneus Orsetti &amp; Lopes-Andrade sp. nov., male holotype. 1, 3 dorsal view 2, 4 ventral view. 3. Head, arrowhead points to excavations of frontal fovea 4. Detail of labial and maxillary palpomeres. Scale bars: 5 mm (1 − 2); 1 mm (3 − 4)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261701/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
); elytra shiny black (
<figureCitation id="13212A4AFF9AFF9899107207FE03AB7C" box="[363,427,845,868]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1827,1849]" captionTargetBox="[201,1368,320,1789]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[192,1395,311,1806]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Pelecium igneus Orsetti &amp; Lopes-Andrade sp. nov., male holotype. 1, 3 dorsal view 2, 4 ventral view. 3. Head, arrowhead points to excavations of frontal fovea 4. Detail of labial and maxillary palpomeres. Scale bars: 5 mm (1 − 2); 1 mm (3 − 4)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261701/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
), glabrous, with only standard setae present (supraorbital, pronotal and parascutellar setae); ventral surface shiny black (
<figureCitation id="13212A4AFF9AFF9899BE723AFDAEAB9F" box="[453,518,880,903]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1827,1849]" captionTargetBox="[201,1368,320,1789]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[192,1395,311,1806]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Pelecium igneus Orsetti &amp; Lopes-Andrade sp. nov., male holotype. 1, 3 dorsal view 2, 4 ventral view. 3. Head, arrowhead points to excavations of frontal fovea 4. Detail of labial and maxillary palpomeres. Scale bars: 5 mm (1 − 2); 1 mm (3 − 4)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261701/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
), 
<emphasis id="B96EEADDFF9AFF989A60723AFDF0AB9F" bold="true" box="[539,600,880,903]" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Head</emphasis>
microreticulate, with a pair of frontal punctiform fovea, each with a short and shallow excavation at the outer side (
<figureCitation id="13212A4AFF9AFF989A4372D8FDD5ABB1" box="[568,637,914,937]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1827,1849]" captionTargetBox="[201,1368,320,1789]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[192,1395,311,1806]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Pelecium igneus Orsetti &amp; Lopes-Andrade sp. nov., male holotype. 1, 3 dorsal view 2, 4 ventral view. 3. Head, arrowhead points to excavations of frontal fovea 4. Detail of labial and maxillary palpomeres. Scale bars: 5 mm (1 − 2); 1 mm (3 − 4)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261701/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
, arrows). 
<emphasis id="B96EEADDFF9AFF989A9572D8FC29ABB1" bold="true" box="[750,897,914,937]" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Mouth parts</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="13212A4AFF9AFF989BE872D8FC71ABB1" box="[915,985,914,937]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1827,1849]" captionTargetBox="[201,1368,320,1789]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[192,1395,311,1806]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Pelecium igneus Orsetti &amp; Lopes-Andrade sp. nov., male holotype. 1, 3 dorsal view 2, 4 ventral view. 3. Head, arrowhead points to excavations of frontal fovea 4. Detail of labial and maxillary palpomeres. Scale bars: 5 mm (1 − 2); 1 mm (3 − 4)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261701/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
): apical labial and maxillary palpomeres triangular, with long and sparse yellowish setae, surface mostly reddish brown, with apicalmost portion yellowish; fourth maxillary palpomere subtriangular, 2.8X as long as the third palpomere, covered with sparse yellowish slender setae, surface reddish brown, with apicalmost portion yellowish. 
<emphasis id="B96EEADDFF9AFF989B5472B0FC0AAC09" bold="true" box="[815,930,1018,1041]" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Pronotum</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="13212A4AFF9AFF989BCD72B0FC51AC09" box="[950,1017,1018,1041]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1827,1849]" captionTargetBox="[201,1368,320,1789]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[192,1395,311,1806]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Pelecium igneus Orsetti &amp; Lopes-Andrade sp. nov., male holotype. 1, 3 dorsal view 2, 4 ventral view. 3. Head, arrowhead points to excavations of frontal fovea 4. Detail of labial and maxillary palpomeres. Scale bars: 5 mm (1 − 2); 1 mm (3 − 4)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261701/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
) subcordate, minutely rough (in low magnification) to transversely microstriate (in magnification above 100X); lateral margins rounded in apical 4/5, sinuate just in front of basal angles; base truncate, with sides strongly oblique towards highly obtuse and blunt basal angles; median line fine and shallow, deeper posteriorly; basal impressions inconspicuous. 
<emphasis id="B96EEADDFF9AFF989C377528FB16AC61" bold="true" box="[1100,1214,1122,1145]" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Scutellum</emphasis>
triangular (
<figureCitation id="13212A4AFF9AFF989D3C7528FA23AC61" box="[1351,1419,1122,1145]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1827,1849]" captionTargetBox="[201,1368,320,1789]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[192,1395,311,1806]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Pelecium igneus Orsetti &amp; Lopes-Andrade sp. nov., male holotype. 1, 3 dorsal view 2, 4 ventral view. 3. Head, arrowhead points to excavations of frontal fovea 4. Detail of labial and maxillary palpomeres. Scale bars: 5 mm (1 − 2); 1 mm (3 − 4)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261701/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
), minutely rough (in low magnification) to microreticulate (in magnification above 100X). 
<emphasis id="B96EEADDFF9AFF989CE775CFFB4DAC84" bold="true" box="[1180,1253,1157,1180]" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Elytra</emphasis>
with inner five interneurs deep; in between interneurs shiny and unpunctate, minutely rough (in low magnification) to transversely microstriate (in magnification above 100X). 
<emphasis id="B96EEADDFF9AFF989A077580FD4DACF9" bold="true" box="[636,741,1226,1249]" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Protibiae</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="13212A4AFF9AFF989A8F7580FC9EACF9" box="[756,822,1226,1249]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1827,1849]" captionTargetBox="[201,1368,320,1789]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[192,1395,311,1806]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Pelecium igneus Orsetti &amp; Lopes-Andrade sp. nov., male holotype. 1, 3 dorsal view 2, 4 ventral view. 3. Head, arrowhead points to excavations of frontal fovea 4. Detail of labial and maxillary palpomeres. Scale bars: 5 mm (1 − 2); 1 mm (3 − 4)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261701/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
) expanded at apex. 
<emphasis id="B96EEADDFF9AFF989C6A7580FB25ACF9" bold="true" box="[1041,1165,1226,1249]" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Mesotibiae</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="13212A4AFF9AFF989CE57580FB77ACF9" box="[1182,1247,1226,1249]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1827,1849]" captionTargetBox="[201,1368,320,1789]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[192,1395,311,1806]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Pelecium igneus Orsetti &amp; Lopes-Andrade sp. nov., male holotype. 1, 3 dorsal view 2, 4 ventral view. 3. Head, arrowhead points to excavations of frontal fovea 4. Detail of labial and maxillary palpomeres. Scale bars: 5 mm (1 − 2); 1 mm (3 − 4)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261701/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
) not expanded at apex; densely pubescent ventrally, more ventroapically. 
<emphasis id="B96EEADDFF9AFF989A8975A7FCC5AD1C" bold="true" box="[754,877,1261,1284]" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Metatibiae</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="13212A4AFF9AFF989B0775A7FC14AD1C" box="[892,956,1261,1284]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1827,1849]" captionTargetBox="[201,1368,320,1789]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[192,1395,311,1806]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Pelecium igneus Orsetti &amp; Lopes-Andrade sp. nov., male holotype. 1, 3 dorsal view 2, 4 ventral view. 3. Head, arrowhead points to excavations of frontal fovea 4. Detail of labial and maxillary palpomeres. Scale bars: 5 mm (1 − 2); 1 mm (3 − 4)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261701/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
) slender, densely pubescent in apical half of ventral side. 
<emphasis id="B96EEADDFF9AFF989964745AFDBBAD3F" bold="true" box="[287,531,1296,1319]" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Abdominal tergite IX</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="13212A4AFF9AFF989A59745AFDC6AD3F" box="[546,622,1296,1319]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 12" captionStartId="3.[151,258,1791,1813]" captionTargetBox="[204,1400,205,1756]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[185,1401,191,1770]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 12. Pelecium igneus Orsetti &amp; Lopes-Andrade sp. nov., male holotype. Aedeagus (5 – 8) 5. Dorsal view 6. Left lateral view 7. Ven tr a l v ie w 8. Right lateral view 9. Penis, right lateral view 10. Left paramere 11. Right paramere 12. Tergite IX. Scale bar: 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261702/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
) oval, asymmetric, with anterior portion narrowed to a sharp apex; posterior portion with asymmetric expansions on each side; posterior edge barely curved and growing to an obtuse angle. 
<emphasis id="B96EEADDFF9AFF9898EC741FFEACAD74" bold="true" box="[151,260,1365,1388]" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Aedeagus</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="13212A4AFF9AFF989969741FFED6AD74" box="[274,382,1364,1388]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 12" captionStartId="3.[151,258,1791,1813]" captionTargetBox="[204,1400,205,1756]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[185,1401,191,1770]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 12. Pelecium igneus Orsetti &amp; Lopes-Andrade sp. nov., male holotype. Aedeagus (5 – 8) 5. Dorsal view 6. Left lateral view 7. Ven tr a l v ie w 8. Right lateral view 9. Penis, right lateral view 10. Left paramere 11. Right paramere 12. Tergite IX. Scale bar: 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261702/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Figs 5−11</figureCitation>
) with 
<emphasis id="B96EEADDFF9AFF9899BF741FFE57AD74" bold="true" box="[452,511,1365,1388]" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">penis</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="13212A4AFF9AFF989A76741FFDC5AD74" box="[525,621,1364,1388]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 12" captionStartId="3.[151,258,1791,1813]" captionTargetBox="[204,1400,205,1756]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[185,1401,191,1770]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 12. Pelecium igneus Orsetti &amp; Lopes-Andrade sp. nov., male holotype. Aedeagus (5 – 8) 5. Dorsal view 6. Left lateral view 7. Ven tr a l v ie w 8. Right lateral view 9. Penis, right lateral view 10. Left paramere 11. Right paramere 12. Tergite IX. Scale bar: 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261702/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Figs 5−9</figureCitation>
) cylindrical, slender, conspicuously curved in lateral views (
<figureCitation id="13212A4AFF9AFF989C8F741FFAC6AD74" box="[1268,1390,1365,1388]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 12" captionStartId="3.[151,258,1791,1813]" captionTargetBox="[204,1400,205,1756]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[185,1401,191,1770]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 12. Pelecium igneus Orsetti &amp; Lopes-Andrade sp. nov., male holotype. Aedeagus (5 – 8) 5. Dorsal view 6. Left lateral view 7. Ven tr a l v ie w 8. Right lateral view 9. Penis, right lateral view 10. Left paramere 11. Right paramere 12. Tergite IX. Scale bar: 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261702/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Figs 6, 8, 9</figureCitation>
), its apical edge straight (
<figureCitation id="13212A4AFF9AFF9899087432FE7AAD97" box="[371,466,1400,1423]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 12" captionStartId="3.[151,258,1791,1813]" captionTargetBox="[204,1400,205,1756]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[185,1401,191,1770]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 12. Pelecium igneus Orsetti &amp; Lopes-Andrade sp. nov., male holotype. Aedeagus (5 – 8) 5. Dorsal view 6. Left lateral view 7. Ven tr a l v ie w 8. Right lateral view 9. Penis, right lateral view 10. Left paramere 11. Right paramere 12. Tergite IX. Scale bar: 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261702/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Figs 5, 7</figureCitation>
); 
<emphasis id="B96EEADDFF9AFF98999C7432FDC8AD97" bold="true" box="[487,608,1400,1423]" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">parameres</emphasis>
asymmetric (
<figureCitation id="13212A4AFF9AFF989A8A7432FC2DAD97" box="[753,901,1399,1423]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 12" captionStartId="3.[151,258,1791,1813]" captionTargetBox="[204,1400,205,1756]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[185,1401,191,1770]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 12. Pelecium igneus Orsetti &amp; Lopes-Andrade sp. nov., male holotype. Aedeagus (5 – 8) 5. Dorsal view 6. Left lateral view 7. Ven tr a l v ie w 8. Right lateral view 9. Penis, right lateral view 10. Left paramere 11. Right paramere 12. Tergite IX. Scale bar: 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261702/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Figs 7, 10−11</figureCitation>
), left paramere (
<figureCitation id="13212A4AFF9AFF989C4E7432FB29AD97" box="[1077,1153,1400,1423]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 12" captionStartId="3.[151,258,1791,1813]" captionTargetBox="[204,1400,205,1756]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[185,1401,191,1770]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 12. Pelecium igneus Orsetti &amp; Lopes-Andrade sp. nov., male holotype. Aedeagus (5 – 8) 5. Dorsal view 6. Left lateral view 7. Ven tr a l v ie w 8. Right lateral view 9. Penis, right lateral view 10. Left paramere 11. Right paramere 12. Tergite IX. Scale bar: 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261702/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
) longer and narrower than right paramere (
<figureCitation id="13212A4AFF9AFF98993A74D0FE27ADA9" box="[321,399,1434,1457]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 12" captionStartId="3.[151,258,1791,1813]" captionTargetBox="[204,1400,205,1756]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[185,1401,191,1770]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 12. Pelecium igneus Orsetti &amp; Lopes-Andrade sp. nov., male holotype. Aedeagus (5 – 8) 5. Dorsal view 6. Left lateral view 7. Ven tr a l v ie w 8. Right lateral view 9. Penis, right lateral view 10. Left paramere 11. Right paramere 12. Tergite IX. Scale bar: 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261702/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
